%S A396918 178,202,224,236,324,428,776,856,1324,1328,1408,1936,2284,2476,2648,
%T A396918 2816
%N A396918 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)*psi(x)^2*phi(x) = x^4 + y^4 + z^4 + t^4 + w^4.
%C A396918 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma*psi^2*phi-quartic quintuple.
%H A396918 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-2-phi-quartic-quintuples/blob/main/A396918">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A396918 (324, 156, 252, 300, 348) is such a quintuple because sigma(324) * psi(324)^2 * phi(324) = 847 * 648^2 * 108 = 324^4 + 156^4 + 252^4 + 300^4 + 348^4.
%o A396918 (Python) # See Links.
